cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DC, cs.AR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category as it focuses on optimizing the performance of deep neural networks through quantization and integer GEMM operations. It may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as deep learning is commonly used in computer vision tasks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as the optimization techniques discussed in the paper can improve the efficiency of distributed deep learning systems. The paper may also fall under cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) as it discusses techniques for improving the performance of GEMM operations, which are critical to running deep learning models on hardware. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it focuses on optimizing the performance of neural networks.
